ygData.subject: Re: [EQ_women] I'm a new member
ygData.msgSnippet: Salutations!  To you too. Sorry about my late response.
ygData.messageBody:
Salutations!

<< Happy New Year to all >>

To you too. Sorry about my late response.

<< I'm new to EQ women and love the fact that
something like this is out there. Soooo tired of
trying to talk EQ talk with guys. Even in the game
they speak a different language. >>

Don't they though. That's part of what I love about my
guild though. There are a few women in it who play a
lot and we've all adopted each other as sisters. Were
a wild and crazy bunch but we have a blast. I'm pretty
new to EQ as well since I've only been on about 3 - 4
months but I'm additcted for sure and get on most
nights for at least a little while.
:o)
Feel free to chat here. I love to talk so I'll be glad
to chat with you.
:o)

<< My name is Sue, I am 43 mother of 3
(grown&gone) kids and have been a gameaholic for
the better part of 25 years. >>

My name is Brangvyne . . . just like my characters
name. It's one nice thing about having a wierd name
like me, you can use it for things like this.
:o)

<< I have a lvl 38 Shaman Vah Shir - Nofreesowforu, a
lvl 6 Human Warrior - Diixii, and a lvl 9 Cleric -
Pletora. All on the Berrel Server. >>

All I have is my wood elf lvl 33 ranger on Xegony and
a 2nd lvl Bard on Chazic Thule (sp)

<< Oh and like all of us I have a "mule" in the
Bazaar. Send me a tell and let the killing begin ')>>

I don't have a mule in the bazaar. Can't keep one up
with my dial up. Maybe someday.

Hugs,
Bran
